Introduction

GTFS feeds are frequency used to support transportation modeling and planning exercises. Before feed is used to represent transportation service, it is important to perform a series of validation steps to ensure that the service represented in the feed is accurate. The purpose of this document is to review the findings of a variety of diagnostics and analytical tests that are intended to help an analyst perform a QA/QC review of GTFS feeds.
